SIMPLE: phototonus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Phototonus
<hw>Pho*tot"o*nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Photo-</er>, and <er>Tone</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A motile condition in plants resulting from exposure to
light.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pho`to*ton"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An irritable condition of
protoplasm, resulting in movement, due to a certain intensity of
light.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Pho`to*ton"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phototopography</ent>⟦br⟧
